<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-16T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Argentina/110:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-16T17:00:00-05:00">January 16, 1942—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>69. From Williams. The Federal Loan Agency has offered a satisfactory
                            basis which should enable the immediate conclusion of the over-all
                            purchase agreement. I am leaving Washington Saturday and should arrive
                            at Rio January 20. I shall explain all details to Sumner Welles.
                            [Williams.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>